  "text": "Found 11 Java source files under clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ in sg-evals/kafka--0753c489 that define classes containing 'Rebalance' in the class name. These files implement the consumer group rebalance protocol across three functional areas: (1) Callback handling: ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker.java invokes user-registered ConsumerRebalanceListener callbacks; ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName.java is an enum of the callback method names (ON_PARTITIONS_REVOKED, ON_PARTITIONS_ASSIGNED, ON_PARTITIONS_LOST). (2) Streams rebalance: StreamsRebalanceData.java holds rebalance state for Kafka Streams; StreamsRebalanceListener.java defines the streams-specific rebalance callback interface; StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker.java invokes streams rebalance callbacks. (3) Metrics: RebalanceMetricsManager.java is the abstract base for rebalance metrics; RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager.java tracks callback timing; ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager.java and ShareRebalanceMetricsManager.java specialize metrics for consumer and share group rebalances. (4) Events: ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent.java and ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent.java are the async event types for rebalance callback coordination between the application and background threads.",
